<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1482,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1482,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="382">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of the subgenus are characterized by the juxta bearing a medial ventral crest, large medial costal protrusion of valva bearing a heavily sclerotised transverse crest (among other subgenera, only 
<taxonomicName authority="Karisch, 2013" authorityName="Karisch" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Strigivulpecula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="382">Strigivulpecula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Karisch, T." box="[268,425,1555,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="382" pagination="39 - 197" refId="ref6947" refString="Karisch, T. (2013) Taxonomic revision of the African Cyana - species (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae, Lithosiinae) (plates 15 - 19). Esperiana, 18, 39 - 197." type="journal article" year="2013">Karisch, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has such a well-developed medial costal protrusion, but with a reduced crest), and robust distal saccular process being strongly curved dorsad. The female genitalia are more characteristic and differ from those of other subgenera by the heavily sclerotised postvaginal plate.
</paragraph>
